					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">euler271 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">anyone can tell me exactly what exactly happens when $2000.7 is cleared?</div>
<br />When you turn off bit 7 of PPUCTRL, the PPU hides its vblank NMI signal from the CPU. That's all. To actually be able to write to VRAM at any time, you need to force blanking. You do this by writing 0 to PPUMASK ($2001).</div>

